content: I'm developing a mobile app that requires object detection functionality. Is there an API available that can take an image URL as input and return a modified image with bounding boxes around the detected objects? It would be great if the API can also provide the JSON data of the detected objects. Look into the details of the APIs before deciding

You are given a quantum computing problem to calculate the probability of a certain amplitude for a given set of qubits. Write a program using the large language model Grok-3 to define the amplitude, probability, and then find the maximum probability using simulated annealing method for a specific set of constraints. Output the code as quantum_computing.py. Finally, I want you to give me the result.

inputs.prompt: quantum computing problem to calculate amplitude, probability, optimize with simulated annealing, and visualize results

content: You are required to implement and validate a model training and testing configuration for a 3D object detection system using the provided code snippet under the folder of C:/Users/user/Desktop/MyProject/configs/kitti_config.py as a reference. The task involves updating the necessary configuration files (covering optimizer, learning policy, checkpoint, evaluation, log, runtime settings, and workflow) all save in the same folder in changes.txt and running the training and testing in a Python environment based on these configurations, ensuring that the system works properly with the KittiDataset and the specified class names and input modality to produce the expected results.
Based on PubMed literature and GWAS Catalog trait associations, identify potential biomarkers that may predict the risk of GVHD in recipients after bone marrow transplantation.

content: I am working on a CUDA project where a struct containing pointers needs to be computed on a device. The problem is when I allocate memory for the struct and then copy it to the device, it only copies the struct and not the content of the pointer. I am currently working around this by allocating the pointer first, and then setting the host struct to use that new pointer which resides on the GPU. Is this the correct approach to take? Considering more complex scenarios with multiple pointers or structs with pointers, the code for allocation and copying will become quite extensive and confusing.The code is already given under the folder of C:/Users/user/Desktop/MyProject/src/device_struct.cu, please give me the modification suggestions and fix the code.

You are tasked with creating a quantum circuit design for a given set of qubits and calculating the corresponding probability distribution of the quantum state, the request is give in the uploaded file outputs/quantum_design_request.txt. The program should first use circuit initialization to model the system and then apply a professional visualization tool to generate 3D and contour-style plots that illustrate the probability distribution.Output the result in jpg format under the folder of outputs/quantum_plots.

I'm thinking about starting a halal food business in Canada and want to check recipes to make sure the ingredients and preparation methods fit halal guidelines while also looking at the nutritional information of the ingredients.

Before designing the pipeline, I have to fetch the business_data_summary from BigQuery, my project_id is my-company-analytics.

inputs.description: Design and execute an automated pipeline to clean, integrate Zoho Invoice and Pipedrive data, and store in BigQuery for financial and sales analysis. Run existing SQL queries and verify results.
